officialTitle: Effectiveness of Transversus Abdominis Plane Block Versus Quadratus Lumborum Technique in Patients After Cesarean Section
inclusionCriteria:
* obtained consent
* singleton pregnancy
* subarachnoid anaesthesia
* Must be FEMALE
* Must have minimum age of 18 Years
* Must have maximum age of 75 Years
exclusionCriteria:
* coagulopathy
* allergy to to local anesthetics
* depression, antidepressant drugs treatment
* epilepsy
* usage of painkiller before surgery
* addiction to alcohol or recreational drugs
